  "stem": "<p>In right triangle <math><mi>D</mi><mi>E</mi><mi>F</mi></math>, angle <math><mi>E</mi></math> is a right angle. The length of side <math><mover><mrow><mi>D</mi><mi>E</mi></mrow><mo>&#175;</mo></mover></math> is <math><mn>24</mn></math>, and the length of side <math><mover><mrow><mi>E</mi><mi>F</mi></mrow><mo>&#175;</mo></mover></math> is <math><mn>18</mn></math>. Which of the following is equal to <math><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>D</mi><mo>)</mo></math>?</p>",
  "answerOptions": [
    {
      "id": "a",
      "content": "<p><math><mi>tan</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>D</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "b",
      "content": "<p><math><mi>cos</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "c",
      "content": "<p><math><mi>cos</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>D</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "d",
      "content": "<p><math><mi>tan</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>"
    }
  ],
  "keys": [
    "b"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p>Choice B is correct. Since angle E is the right angle, angles D and F are complementary. The sine of an angle equals the cosine of its complement, so sin(D) = cos(F).</p><p>The other choices confuse tangent with sine or pair the trigonometric ratio with the same angle.</p>",
